High blood pressure (hypertension) can be caused by a mix of lifestyle factors, medical conditions, and genetics. Here are the common causes:

1. Lifestyle Factors
High salt intake

Lack of physical activity

Being overweight or obese

Excessive alcohol consumption

Smoking

Chronic stress

2. Medical Conditions
Kidney disease

Diabetes

Thyroid disorders

Sleep apnea

Adrenal gland tumors

3. Medications
Certain prescription or over-the-counter drugs, like:

NSAIDs (e.g., ibuprofen)

Birth control pills

Decongestants

Some antidepressants

4. Genetics & Age
Family history of hypertension

Risk increases with age
